<TEXT>
mayor kurt schmoke removed the baltimore school 
board president on tuesday after he admitted lying to board members 
as a way of finding out who leaks stories to the media 
meldon s hollis who was appointed by the mayor to a oneyear 
term as board president in december will remain on the board the 
mayor appoints the nine board members who serve as volunteers 
hollis an attorney admitted earlier tuesday that he used poor 
judgment in planting three different versions of a story to track 
down news leaks and said that he would resign if the mayor asked 
him to 
whether or not i retain the public confidence is a 
matter for the public to decide for the mayor to decide and for 
the school board to decide hollis said at a news conference 
tuesday afternoon 
schmoke called hollis actions a terrible mistake in 
judgment 
my view is that the public can tolerate an official being 
wrong on an issue schmoke said what people generally find 
intolerable is an official lying to them 
tape recordings of holliss remarks monday to the foundation for 
community unity in service a political club show he said he 
leaked false information to school board members to see if they 
were lying to me 
i know whos doing the lying he said in the speech i 
know who it is i feed them the lies then they run out and lie to 
the press 
hollis said tuesday he could not recall using the word lie 
in describing the way he released information on how candidates for 
school superintendent would be interviewed earlier this year 
he said he believed leaks were undermining the selection 
process because some candidates threatened to withdraw if their 
candidacies were made public 
he said he had become a political target and the object of news 
leaks because of his attempts to uncover favoritism in the awarding 
of grants in the school system 
board member edward j gutman said tuesday that he was 
bewildered by hollis remarks 
i think theres something wrong with the man i dont even 
know what hes talking about gutman said the whole thing is 
getting uglier and uglier we are trustees with the most 
important responsibility in the city 
some board members hollis said walk out of meetings and tell 
you we have a deal and then before i can get to my office the press 
is calling me asking me did you all decide so and so 
i know who they are i know who is doing the leaking i know 
who is doing the lying thats ok it will be taken care of in 
time hollis said 
hollis acknowledged dissension within the board however he 
took issue with an article in mondays editions of the baltimore 
sun which said the school board was in a revolt 
problems arose last spring between hollis and board members when 
they were prevented from participating in the selection of a new 
school superintendent problems resurfaced in july when hollis 
decided to hire a new executive director and several board members 
said they felt the full board should have voted on the post 
