a strong earthquake with a preliminary reading of 
53 on the richter scale shook an uninhabited island in the pacific 
ocean this morning the central meteorological agency said 
the tremor occurred at 959 am 859 am edt monday and was 
centered at 275 miles under the seabed near the japanese island of 
torishima about 360 miles south of tokyo in the capital the 
tremor jiggled furniture in skyscrapers but went unnoticed by most 
people no injuries were reported 
the agency said there was no danger of tidal waves 
the richter scale measures the magnitude of a quake at its 
epicenter according to ground motion as recorded on seismographs 
an earthquake registering 5 on the richter scale is considered 
very strong and a 6 severe capable of widespread damage 
near the epicenter 
