<TEXT>
heavy combat in northern rebel 
strongholds killed or wounded more than 80 leftists guerrillas and 
government troops a military spokesman said today 
col galileo torres said guerrillas attacked the el paraiso 
garrison headquarters of the 4th army brigade in chalatenango 
province at 105 am with mortar fire 
nine soldiers and five guerrillas died in the attack 37 miles 
north of the capital of san salvador and 12 government troops were 
wounded he said 
torres head of the armed forces press office also said there 
were a series of clashes in northern morazan province between 
government units and guerrillas 
the rebels suffered 50 casualties in morazan and five soldiers 
were wounded he said in a telephone interview 
both provinces are strongholds of the rebel faribuno marti 
national liberation front where guerrillas move freely and even 
exercise some administration of towns and villages 
he said the fighting at el paraiso lasted two hours and officers 
on the scene believed quite a few rebels were wounded the 
bodies of five rebels and six m16 assault rifles were recovered 
torres said 
it was the first guerrilla attack on a brigade headquarters 
since a february assault on the 3rd brigade in eastern usulutan 
province 
a us military adviser the first to die in combat was killed 
at el paraiso in march 1987 when rebels penetrated the base 
killing 70 government soldiers there are several dozen us 
military advisers at bases in chalatenango 
torres said the fighting in morazan began at 4 pm monday and 
lasted until 3 am tuesday he called it a series of encounters 
between three government commando units of about 15 men each and a 
significant guerrilla column 
helicopters ferrying wounded soldiers and supplies were still 
coming under fire several hours after the main clashes ended he 
said and troops were still mopping up around gigante hill outside 
perquin 125 miles northeast of san salvador 
he said col emilio ponce commander of the eastern military 
zone told him at midmorning there was still no breakdown between 
dead and wounded in the 50 guerrilla casualities he said he did 
not know how many bodies had been recovered 
there was no way to immediately confirm the official casualty 
figures 
earlier this month the military claimed 25 rebels dead near 
tejutepeque in central el salvador but reporters at the scene 
confirmed only four dead precise casualties are also hard to pin 
down because the rebels try to remove their dead from the 
battlefield 
