<TEXT>
massachusetts has slipped from first place to 
10th in the past year among states with the lowest unemployment 
rates while neighboring vermont emerged as the best job provider 
for its residents according to a government report issued tuesday 
with an unemployment rate of just 23 percent in july and just 
6900 of its workers lacking jobs vermont replaced new hampshire 
as the state with the lowest joblessness the bureau of labor 
statistics said 
new hampshire whose jobless rate climbed from 2 percent in june 
to 25 percent in july had been leading the nation with the lowest 
unemployment since last october 
massachusetts unemployment rate meanwhile rose from 34 
percent in june to 36 percent in july it was a full percentage 
point higher that the same month a year ago when it held the title 
as the state with the lowest joblessness 
the number of jobless in massachusetts climbed by more than 
25000 to 155600 over the year despite the addition of nearly 
60000 new jobs in the state according to the bls data 
following vermont and new hampshire with the lowest unemployment 
rates in july were hawaii and delaware at 31 percent each 
connecticut and north carolina at 32 percent each rhode island at 
33 percent nebraska at 34 percent and minnesota at 35 percent 
louisiana continued to be the only state with doubledigit 
joblessness 102 percent in july down from 106 percent a month 
earlier 
kentucky new mexico and west virginia all had unemployment 
rates above 8 percent compared with a nationwide jobless rate of 
55 percent for the month the bureau said all of the figures are 
unadjusted for seasonal variations 
while the jobless rate nationwide declined 06 percentage point 
over the year it dropped much more dramatically in several states 
mississippi wyoming idaho and texas all saw their unemployment 
rates drop by more than 2 full percentage points in the 12 months 
unemployment rates over the year rose in only three states 
massachusetts georgia and arkansas 
states with the largest job growth over the year were nevada up 
61 percent delaware up 5 percent florida and maine both up 47 
percent and washington up 44 percent 
the bureau said service type employment increased in virtually 
all of the states while 80 percent of them also showed gains in 
manufacturing transportation trade and government jobs 
cities with the lowest jobless rate in the country were 
burlington vt at 18 percent and stamford conn at 2 percent 
flint mich had the highest unemployment rate at 149 percent 
followed by the mcallenedinburgmission area of texas at 148 
percent 
