mentally ill noted that her organization is made up of 70000 
families of people suffering from mental illness 
for us the lack of services is a personal and family 
tragedy she said 
the overall state rankings were based on a composite figure 
drawn by awarding points ranging from zero to five in each of four 
categories hospital care outpatient services rehabilitation and 
housing 
the report relied on questionnaires to state mental health 
directors various government surveys and visits to 35 states and 
the district of columbia the report said 82 percent of the state 
mental health directors returned ninepage questionnaires when 
guaranteed anonymity even though their national organization did 
not endorse the survey 
