<TEXT>
the pentagon has recreated a tiny slice of 
the soviet military machine to serve as a mobile laboratory for 
testing american weapons and equipment 
the unusual amalgamation of enemy gear is now undergoing its 
first operational test at kirtland air force base nm the 
pentagon announced tuesday 
known formally as the mobile integrated threat test the setup 
replicates a key slice of a soviet army headquarters and division 
organization and uses real enemy equipment obtained through a 
variety of means officials said 
most of the equipment is electronic primarily radar and radio 
gear but mig jet fighters also will be used in simulating the 
threat force the pentagon added in a statement 
the us military has long conducted tests and experiments with 
pieces of military equipment made in the soviet union warsaw pact 
and third world countries and then captured stolen or covertly 
purchased 
what makes the new effort different is an attempt to combine the 
radar radios and targeting equipment into the type of 
integrated system that us forces would face on a battlefield 
also setting the work apart is the creation of a small 
organization known as the defense test and evaluation support 
agency that is responsible for operating the gear and playing the 
enemy 
were not reinventing the wheel bits and portions of this 
have been done in the past said james wilson the director of 
the mobile integrated threat test 
what were going to offer is the ability to deliver set up 
and operate this enemy gear for testing us systems were 
trying to come close to the real thing the gear we have is not 
stateoftheart but its still in use within the warsaw pact 
the tests now under way at kirtland are designed to demonstrate 
that a relatively large network of soviet equipment can be operated 
just like the russians would handle it once that goal is 
accomplished the support agency will respond to requests from the 
military services for assistance in checking out the effectiveness 
of various types of american equipment 
the kirtland tests which will run to early october will 
include some flights by soviet aircraft simulating closeair 
support missions as well as flights by new mexico air national 
guard a7 attack jets 
the a7s will be used to test the capabilities of the soviet 
sensors the pentagon statement said 
but this is not a traveling road show wilson said there 
wont be any dogfights or anything like that we dont want to 
oversell what were doing 
</TEXT>
