<TEXT>
roger hargreaves who turned his deskpad doodlings 
into the popular mister men and little miss storybooks for 
children died of a heart attack at his home near london death 
notices said tuesday he was 53 
the times of london said hargreaves died monday 
hargreaves a laundrymans son was born in the northern english 
county of yorkshire and went into advertising after service in the 
royal air force his career prospered but he said boredom turned 
him to writing childrens stories 
combining his doodles with bedtime stories he made up for his 
own children it took hargreaves just two weeks to find a publisher 
and in 1972 his first six stories went on sale they introduced 
young readers to mister bump mister strong and mister sneezy 
in 1981 he began a series featuring such characters as little 
miss fussy and little miss sunshine 
his texts were simple and his drawings childlike bold colors 
a few lines some squares and dots 
the books published in soft cover were inexpensive 
some 85 million are in circulation translated into 22 languages 
the stories have more than 750 characters and spinoffs include a 
television cartoon series and childrens cups and plates 
stationery and clothing 
hargreaves is survived by a wife two daughters two sons and a 
granddaughter 
</TEXT>
