<TEXT>
crop futures prices closed mostly higher tuesday 
on the chicago board of trade as strength from the buoyant wheat 
market spilled over into the corn and soybean pits 
corn and soybean futures had opened lower in reaction to the 
agriculture departments higherthanexpected harvest estimates 
issued after the close of trading on monday 
the report estimated 1988 us corn production at 446 billion 
bushels and soybean production at 147 billion bushels the numbers 
represent sharp declines from last years production levels because 
of drought damage but were still above most private forecasts 
the usdas wheatproduction estimate also was higher than 
expected but wheat futures prices rallied on the reports 
predictions of declining soviet and canadian wheat production and 
