<TEXT>
ecuador plans to seek an increase in its 
opec production quota energy minister diego tamariz said tuesday 
noting that government budget plans did not account for the recent 
decline in world oil prices 
tamariz said the average price ecuador gets for its oil has been 
ranging between 1188 and ll55 a barrel while the governments 
budget was calculated on an estimate of 17 a barrel 
there is a certain weakness in the petroleum market that has 
accentuated in recent days with a declining tendency tamariz 
said in a news conference 
ecuador is one of the smallest producers among the 13 members of 
the organization of petroleum exporting countries although oil 
provides more than half of its export earnings 
the energy minister said ecuador planned to ask opec to increase 
its production quota from 210000 barrels daily to between 300000 
and 310000 barrels 
ecuador currently produces 310000 barrels a day with special 
permission from opec which ends this month opec approved the 
temporary increase in ecuadors production after the country 
suffered devastating economic damage from earthquakes in march 1987 
tamariz said the market was unstable because of peace 
negotiations between iran and iraq which are among the worlds 
major oil producers 
overall opec production in august was estimated at 20 million 
barrels a day nearly 35 million barrels over its selfimposed 
output ceiling the world oil glut plus speculation that the 
ceasefire in the iraniraq war could bring even higher production 
has helped depress prices below opecs benchmark of 18 a barrel 
in addition to ecuador the united arab emirates is seeking a 
higher quota the uae has refused to accept a quota of 948000 
barrels a day and demanded a 15 millionbarrel quota roughly the 
level of its current production 
</TEXT>
