<TEXT>
a defendant utility in the washington 
public power supply system fraud trial settled its share of the 
case for 65 million in an agreement announced late tuesday the 
day before opening arguments were set to begin in federal court 
the settlement by washingtons clallam county public utility 
district left 19 other defendants including 16 utilities to stand 
trial in the fraud suit stemming from the biggest municipal bond 
default ever 
settlements so far total more than 353 million and have 
included more than 70 utilities and wall street firms that handled 
wppss bond sales plaintiffs also have assumed rights to disputed 
insurance claims that could yield another 92 million 
opening trial statements were expected to last through thursday 
the first witness is expected to take the stand monday 
bondholders originally sued more than 100 parties in the case 
which grew out of wppss 1983 default on 225 billion worth of 
bonds sold to finance construction on two neverfinished nuclear 
power plants wppss nos 4 and 5 
the defendants have denied the claims of fraud arguing that 
poor judgment may have been a factor but wppss and defendant 
utilities acted in what they believed were the best interests of 
the northwests energy needs 
in addition to the 16 utilities which were both wppss board 
members and participants in building plants 4 and 5 remaining 
defendants include two engineering firms and a financial adviser to 
the supply system 
mel weiss an attorney for plaintiff wppss bond buyers said 
clallam county pud would pay 6 million cash and another 521750 
would come from its insuror clallam pud commissioners still must 
formally approve the settlement weiss said 
officials of the port angeles washbased utility were not 
immediately available for comment 
this is a significant settlement in that its a first with a 
member thats basically uninsured said weiss 
it shows the utilities can raise significant amounts of money 
without insurance he said 
the clallam pud settlement also could indicate what the entire 
wppss suit might be settled for weiss said clallam pud paid 475 
million per percentage point of its 14 percent interest in two 
wppss nuclear plants 
the 16 remaining utilities contracted for about 63 percent of 
the plants expected output so a final settlement could total 
about 300 million 
settlement talks have been conducted in secrecy so it is 
unknown which defendants are negotiating 
</TEXT>
